# docs/ is mostly heavy internal documentation (qa, dev, functional,
# technical, training, archive, product, ...) that the deployed bundle
# does NOT read. Excluded from the image to keep it small.
#
# However, three subtrees are read by the running app at request time
# and MUST ship in the image, or the corresponding routes return 500:
#   - docs/changelog/  — src/lib/changelog/loader.ts → /changelog page
#   - docs/api/        — src/app/api/v1/openapi.{json,yaml}/route.ts
#                        and the public-API documentation links from
#                        /sandbox + /api/v1/openapi.json
#   - docs/planning/   — src/lib/ai/knowledge-base.ts (RAG corpus for
#                        the conversational assistants)
#
# This is the structural fix for DEF-0012 (the dockerignore
# previously dropped ALL of docs/, hidden in production by DEF-0008's
# blanket /changelog → /auth/signin redirect; closing DEF-0008 made
# the 500 visible to Pillar S on the very first run).
#
# Anti-weakening (per `src/lib/public-routes.ts` + ADR 0028): adding
# any new `process.cwd()`-relative read of `docs/<X>` from `src/**`
# REQUIRES a paired `!docs/<X>/**` un-exclude here AND a Pillar S
# spec that probes the corresponding route. Hand-maintained
# divergence between this file and the runtime loaders is a §4.2
# violation and grounds for revert.
docs/**
!docs/changelog/
!docs/changelog/**
!docs/api/
!docs/api/**
!docs/planning/
!docs/planning/**
